This paper is about automatic story generation using natural language processing techniques, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms to generate coherent and diverse stories, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of planning strategies to generate stories, which is related to the field of planning and scheduling (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the generated stories using both automatic and human evaluations, which is related to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.SD).
